reviews.review_text: Great Bistro! I used to come here two years ago, I visited this place recently and it's still the same, same taste same vibe and same pricing. The food is great and tasty, their burger looks basic by the look but if you take a bite out of it, it's very tasty with the patty being crispy, yummy burger sauce, lettuce, onions and pickles! I love their Mexican fries, they are fries in Mexican sauce with pieces of chicken, pickles, olives, gratted cheese and other miscellaneous stuff. Overall a great place to come, also it is crowded at lunch times, many students come and eat here. Recommend!
The ambience is nice over here. Nice place to hangout with friends, but congested. Place is very small. The Food was okay. AC was not working when I visited.

The food here is fantastic—flavorful, fresh, and clearly made with care. The prices are reasonable for the quality you're getting, which makes it a great spot for a satisfying meal. However, the biggest downside is the limited seating. The space is incredibly small, with only a few tables available, which can make dining here feel cramped and uncomfortable, especially during busy times. While the food definitely makes up for a lot, it would be great if they could expand the seating area to accommodate more customers. If you're okay with the tight quarters, though, it’s definitely worth a visit for the great food!
